# Git

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```txt
<type>(scope): description
```

## Types

`feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `chore`, `test`, `build`, `ci`

## Examples

```txt
feat(world): add reusable room component
refactor(primitives): extract floor component
fix(camera): correct controls
docs(roadmap): update milestones
```

## Before every commit

- Ensure the project builds (`npm run build`).
- Review the diff.
- Remove debug code and temporary logging.
- One logical change per commit.
- Keep the subject line under 72 characters.
- Never use vague messages like "fix stuff", "updates", or "wip".

Only commit when explicitly asked.

## Branches

Use lowercase kebab-case with dashes. Never use spaces.

```txt
initial-build
feat-room-generation
fix-camera-controls
```

If a branch name would contain spaces, replace them with dashes (e.g. `initial build` → `initial-build`).
